minimum = min(dataset1['Infected (Last 24 Hours)']) # formula to find minimum value of Deaths
q1 = dataset1['Infected (Last 24 Hours)'].quantile(0.25) #percentile25(1st quartile of Deaths)
q3 = dataset1['Infected (Last 24 Hours)'].quantile(0.75) #percentile75(3rd quartile of Deaths)
iqr = q3 - q1 #formula of interquartile range of Deaths
lower_limit = (q1 - (1.5 * iqr)) # formula of lower limit of Deaths
upper_limit = (q3 + (1.5 * iqr)) # formula of upper limit of Deaths
maximum = max(dataset1['Infected (Last 24 Hours)']) # formula to find maximum value of Deaths

print('Lower Limit: ',lower_limit) # print lower limit of Deaths
print('Minimum Value: ',minimum) # print minimum value of Deaths
print('First Quartile(Q1): ',q1) #print 1st quartile of Deaths
print('Third Quartile(Q3): ',q3) #print 3rd quartile of Deaths
print('Upper Limit: ',upper_limit) # print upper limit of Deaths
print('Maximum: ',maximum) # print maximum value of Deaths
print('Interquartile Range(IQR): ',iqr) #print interquartile range of Deaths

c_list=[] # assign an empty array of name c_list(smoothened cumulative list)

    y = y + yhat1[x] # calculate Smoothened cumulative 
    cr = math.trunc(y) # truncate and remove decimal points and round the value of Smoothened Cumulative
    c_list.append(cr) # insert the elements in the c_list array

c_list1=[] # assign an empty array of name c_list1(smoothened cumulative list)
y_hat1=[] # assign an empty array of name y_hat1(smoothened value)
y = 0 # variable y with value 0

for x in range(0,len(y1)): # for loop
    y = y + yhat1[x] # calculate Smoothened cumulative  
    cr1 = math.trunc(y) # truncate and remove decimal points and round the value of Smoothened Cumulative
    c_list1.append(cr1) # insert the elements in the c_list1 array
    yhr1 = math.trunc(yhat1[x]) # truncate and remove decimal points and round the Smoothened Value
    y_hat1.append(yhr1) # insert the elements in the y_hat1 array

print('\nReporting Date      | Infected (Last 24 Hours) | Smoothened Value | Smoothened Cumulative') # print heading
print('------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------') # print broken line
smooth_table_output1 = "\n".join("{} |        {}               | {}              | {}".format(a, b, c, d) for a, b, c, d in zip(x1, y1, y_hat1, c_list1)) # joining table
print(smooth_table_output1) # print smooth_table_output1 after joining

c_list2=[] # assign an empty array of name c_list2(smoothened cumulative list)
y_hat2=[] # assign an empty array of name y_hat2(smoothened value)
y = 0 # variable y with value 0

for x in range(0,len(y1)): # for loop
    y = y + yhat1[x] # calculate Smoothened cumulative  
    cr2 = math.trunc(y) # truncate and remove decimal points and round the value of Smoothened Cumulative
    c_list2.append(cr2) # insert the elements in the c_list2 array
    yhr2 = math.trunc(yhat1[x]) # truncate and remove decimal points and round the Smoothened Value
    y_hat2.append(yhr2) # insert the elements in the y_hat2 array

print('\nReporting Date      | Infected (Last 24 Hours) | Smoothened Value | Smoothened Cumulative') # print heading
print('------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------') # print broken line
smooth_table_output2 = "\n".join("{} |        {}               | {}              | {}".format(a, b, c, d) for a, b, c, d in zip(x1, y1, y_hat2, c_list2)) # joining table
print(smooth_table_output2)# print smooth_table_output2 after joining

c_list3=[] # assign an empty array of name c_list3(smoothened cumulative list)
y_hat3=[] # assign an empty array of name y_hat3(smoothened value)
y = 0 # variable y with value 0 

for x in range(0,len(y1)): # for loop
    y = y + yhat2[x] # calculate Smoothened cumulative  
    cr3 = math.trunc(y) # truncate and remove decimal points and round the value of Smoothened Cumulative
    c_list3.append(cr3) # insert the elements in the c_list3 array
    yhr3 = math.trunc(yhat2[x]) # truncate and remove decimal points and round the Smoothened Value
    y_hat3.append(yhr3) # insert the elements in the y_hat3 array

print('\nReporting Date      | Deaths (Last 24 Hours)  | Smoothened Value      | Smoothened Cumulative') # print heading
print('------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------') # print broken line
smooth_table_output3 = "\n".join("{} |        {}               | {}                    | {}".format(a, b, c, d) for a, b, c, d in zip(x2, y2, y_hat3, c_list3)) # joining table
print(smooth_table_output3) # print smooth_table_output3 after joining 
fig11, ax11 = plt.subplots(figsize = (20, 10)) # create a figure and axis

ax11.set_xlabel('Reporting Date') # label of x-axis
ax11.set_ylabel('Smoothened Cumulative of Deaths') # label of y-axis
plt.plot(x2,c_list3) # Plot Smoothened Cumulative vs Reporting Date graph
plt.show() #show graph

Table with Smoothened Cumulative of Deaths vs Reporting Date graph for Polynomial Order 4

c_list4=[] # assign an empty array of name c_list4(smoothened cumulative list)
y_hat4=[] # assign an empty array of name y_hat4(smoothened value)
y = 0 # variable y with value 0   

for x in range(0,len(y1)): # for loop
    y = y + yhat2[x] # calculate Smoothened cumulative  
    cr4 = math.trunc(y) # truncate and remove decimal points and round the value of Smoothened Cumulative
    c_list4.append(cr4) # insert the elements in the c_list4 array
    yhr4 = math.trunc(yhat2[x]) # truncate and remove decimal points and round the Smoothened Value
    y_hat4.append(yhr4) # insert the elements in the y_hat4 array

print('\nReporting Date      | Deaths (Last 24 Hours)  | Smoothened Value      | Smoothened Cumulative') # print heading
print('------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------') # print broken line
smooth_table_output4 = "\n".join("{} |        {}               | {}                    | {}".format(a, b, c, d) for a, b, c, d in zip(x2, y2, y_hat4, c_list4)) # joining table
print(smooth_table_output4) # print smooth_table_output4 after joining

c_list5=[] # assign an empty array of name c_list5(smoothened cumulative list)
y_hat5=[] # assign an empty array of name y_hat5(smoothened value)

    y = y + yhat2[x] # calculate Smoothened cumulative
    cr5 = math.trunc(y) # truncate and remove decimal points and round the value of Smoothened Cumulative
    c_list5.append(cr5) # insert the elements in the c_list5 array

Applying SIRD Model on Infected Smoothened Cumulative - Polynomial Order 3

In [36]:
ydata = c_list # assign c_list(infected smoothened cumulative list) into ydata variable
xdata = dataset['Days since the first case'] # assign Days since the first case column from dataset into xdata variable
ci = dataset['Infected (Cumulative)'] - 779000 # assign Infected (Cumulative) column from dataset into ci variable

ydata = np.array(ydata, dtype=float) # ydata array with type float
xdata = np.array(xdata, dtype=float) # xdata array with type float
 
#declaring the ODEs
def sird_model(y, x, beta, gamma, delta):
    S = -beta * y[0] * y[1] / N
    R = gamma * y[1]
    D = delta * y[1]
    I = -(S + R + D)
    return S, I, R, D
 
#integrating
def fit_odeint(x, beta, delta):
    return integrate.odeint(sird_model, (S0, I0, R0, D0), x, args=(beta, gamma, delta))[:,1]
 
#parameters
N = 1.0
I0 = ydata[0]
S0 = N - I0
R0 = 0.0
D0 = 0.0
gamma = 1.0/14.0
 
#fitting the model with data
popt, pcov = optimize.curve_fit(fit_odeint, xdata, ydata)
print(popt[0], popt[1]) 
fitted = fit_odeint(xdata, *popt)
 
#plotting the curves
plt.figure(figsize=[16.18,10]);
plt.grid() # show grid line on graph
plt.plot(xdata, ydata, 'ro') # plot Infected smoothened cumulative list vs Days since the first case graph
#plt.plot(xdata, fitted, 'xkcd:blue') # plot fitted vs Days since the first case graph with blue line 
plt.plot(xdata, ci, 'xkcd:green') # plot Infected (Cumulative) vs Days since the first case graph with green line 
#plt.xlim(475, 525) # zoom to x-axis from 475 to 525 
#print(fitted)
plt.xlabel("Time in days") # label of x-axis
plt.ylabel("Smoothened Cumulative of Infected") # label of y-axis
plt.title("SIRD model fitted to Smoothened Cumulative and Infected (Cumulative) - Polynomial Order 3") # set title
plt.show() # show graph
